headline.main: JAPANESE CLOSING PINCERS IN CHINA; Claim They Are Now 30 Miles Apart on Railway -- Drive on Fukien Looming PUSH IN NORTH KIANGSI Enemy Believed Attempting to Increase Pressure on the Railroad in Campaign

lead_paragraph: CHUNGKING, China, June 30 (AP) -- Japanese forces in Kiangsi Province appeared tonight to have opened a new phase of their East China campaign with indications that the coastal province of Fukien might be their next objective.
